Sweet Goodbye to 2022 ♥️🪩

So much to be said about this past year… so much that this tiny little box can’t contain it all. So, I’ll say this.. 

This year alone, I took over 17k photos on my phone.. my heart fills with emotions looking back on all the wonderful memories we made as a family.

From completing renovating our new home, moving, countless birthdays & celebrations, trips to our favorite places with our favorite people, starting Kate Halicki Designs, making new friends & getting to call them family, weddings & new babies, to our extended stays at MedCity… this year alone brought us so much joy & happiness, all the while testing our faith…but it brought us closer as a family & allowed us to see once again what truly matters in this life. 

It’s not what’s on your screen, let me tell you that much. Look up, it’s what’s around you. ♥️ 

Happy New Year my Loves, may this year bring you well wishes & all the luck 🍀🐰

Trigger Warning ❤️‍🩹 

Today marks the beginning of heart month, although, that’s really every month for us. 

To most, this will mean nothing. To others, everything. 

This month comes with a lot of emotions, honestly, too many. So many that I have to take deep, quivering breaths to make sure these emotions don’t get the best of my reality. 

But, even with all of these emotions, I will always feel an immense gratitude for the gift of life for Harrison. I will always be supremely & utterly grateful for our team of doctors, nurses & staff at Medical City, as well as, our family & friends that don’t just let our reality be a past memory that “happened” to Harrison. 

I don’t share every bit of our journey, our check-ups, our battles with weekly sickness, having panic attacks on vacations because his O2 is off, or we need more medication for his treatments… it’s all behind the scenes because some days it’s so overwhelming. Any #heartmom will contest to this. 

So, with that being said…let’s be more aware of our hearts! You go to the dentist right? What about the Dr. when you have a cold? Do you go to the dermatologist, gynecologist, urologist? Get botox, facials, massages or fillers? Then you owe it to yourself to GET YOUR HEART CHECKED!! ♥️ Get your children’s hearts checked, follow-up with your parents, your friends… the people you care about. It’s one appointment, once a year. Just do it, do for those fighting, do it for our angels.

Forever bringing gifts to the treasure chest ♥️

Today… we made someone’s day, we put a smile on a child’s face, we fed an overworked nurse, we provided hot coffee to a tired mama & maybe, just maybe… we made an impact on someone & gave them hope. ♥️ 

With your help, today we brought our CICU family tons of goodies for the unit: @chickfila for the staff & families to fill their bellies, heart cookies by @dallascustomcookies to give them comfort, donated toys to add to the treasure chest & individual gifts for those currently in the unit (with the help of @joycreativeshop ) to know they are OH SO LOVED by their fellow Heart Warrior & Friend Harrison ❤️‍🩹 & ALL OF YOU! 

My heart could burst!! Thank you to everyone that donated, it all went to an amazing team & to families that now know they have an army standing with them praying & lifting up their tiny warriors. ♥️

Jeremiah 29:11

The best thing I get to do, is love you ♥️

My Letter to Holland: 

I can’t believe we’re already here… it seems like yesterday I told your Daddy I was pregnant with you & yet, here we are.

Watching you grow is one of the biggest blessing in life that I’ll never take for granted. As they say, the days are long but the years are fast. That rings true more today than ever… seeing you walk across a stage to graduate & head into KINDERGARTEN is going to bring on a new wave of emotions… and as we all know, mama has the biggest ones. 

Holland Katherine, you my angel are incredibly smart, loving & kind to those all around you. You never not go out of your way or in most cases, not yell across a parking lot to compliment someone… whether it be their hair, shoes or lipstick. 

You wear your emotions on your sleeve (something you clearly get from me) but you have a resilience about you and incredible wit that will take you far in life (that of which you get from your Daddy). 

You imagine big & love even bigger. Something I pray you never lose. 

As you start this new chapter in life (which truth be told..scares me to death)…I pray that God gives you strength to overcome any & all adversities, guidance to do the right thing, patience to persevere & faith that no matter what comes, Dada & I will grow & guide you through it all. 

Happy Graduation Day my Little Princess Monkey-Pig Pumpkin Tot 👩🏼‍🎓 Mama & Dada love you BIG ♥️
.
.
.
.

❤️‍🩹THREE CHEERS for THREE YEARS❤️‍🩹 
HAPPY HEALTHY 🥉 HEART ANNIVERSARY!! 

July came & went… which is why I forgot to post these. But it did not go without us celebrating our favorite Heart Warrior in a BIG way! 

My little warrior, you my darling are moving mountains. You continue to amaze me every single day with how far you’ve come. You’ve been through so much in such a short time on this earth, you’ve fought battles only me & your Daddy know of. You’ve overcome the toughest illnesses & done so with the sweetest & most goofy smile. You’re my hero & always will be. 

You are a constant reminder that things in life happen to make one realize their true potential, their true strength, willpower, value & above all, faith. 

We’ve been tried, tested & truly know the meaning of “life can change in the blink of an eye.” For that, we’ve become forever grateful for the little things in life & have placed the bigger things in God’s hands. 

Harrison Paul, you’re a light in this world. Never let anyone dim it.♥️

Let’s just say I ugly cried… 🩷

Sat down at dinner tonight to only look across a couple of tables & instantly spot @abbey_northcutt smile. I was 1000% sure it was her, Paul wasn’t convinced. Only because he had never had the chance to see her smile. #thankscovid  But as you can see, it’s absolutely contagious. 

I stared at “her” for at least 45 mins, & finally decided to message Abbey on Instagram to only wait another 30 mins (because she has manners & doesn’t look at her phone at dinner) before we finally finished dinner & got up to leave. 

I had already planned on what to say in the event it was her or wasn’t… 

Two steps away from her table, her mouth dropped and she immediately started to get up. It was her. Everything I had planned on saying went to shambles & all I could get out was a burst of tears as my face went into my hands. 

We gave each other a big hug, I honestly don’t even remember what I said but I do know I ugly cried in front of everyone. 

But for those of you new here, Abbey cared for Harrison in the CICU. 

She was there for us during our darkest days & she’s been there during our best. She has seen a side of me, no one has. She’s apart of our story & always will be. She’s family. 

We love you @abbey_northcutt ❤️‍🩹🩺🩹& seeing you tonight *not in the hospital* was something oh so special. ♥️🫶🏻♥️ God knew I needed you today.

& just like that… I blinked. 🍎🥺

Holland’s 1st Day of Kindergarten 📚📝 & Harrisons 1st Day of Toddler 3 🖍️📚- 

I thought I knew heartache & pain, but nothing prepared me for this. Leaving Holland at a new school with new friends, new teachers… new everything. 

Walking away felt the same as when I had to leave the hospital without Harrison. I was leaving my baby girl & I felt completely paralyzed with fear. 

Did I hold it together? No. Did I cry the entire walk back to my car? Absolutely. Did I cry the whole day, I sure did. 

& in the midst of my fears for Holland, we as a family received unfortunate news that my Aunt had passed & it truly brought me to my knees. 

Life is fleeting. I remember being Holland’s age & getting to ride with my *cool aunt* in her convertible, looking at Christmas lights & eating McDonalds chicken nuggets. My Aunt would comment or like every post & heart every single instastory of mine, every.single.one. - I’m going to miss that. 

Time is a thief. If you don’t cherish it, you’ll lose it & all it’s worth. 

Today, I dropped Holland off again only to hate it just as much, maybe more than yesterday. I’m in unchartered waters as a Mama, I’ve never been here before & no one can prepare you for this. No one could prepare me for this, that’s for sure.

Either you drop them off & wave goodbye as if another day… or you’re me. A basket case with dark circles under your eyes that look like you’ve been punched a few times & excedrin you’re popping like tic-tacs. 

Regardless, this is our new. I know Holland is going to thrive, but you better believe I have BIG prayers for her, her administration, teachers & her classmates. 🙏🏻♥️ 

Thank you @magnoliaboonepaperie for the sweetest custom sign & @cecilandlou for our first day outfits ♥️🍎♥️
